This paper deals with wireless networks and their throughput, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of physical-layer network coding (PNC) also falls under these sub-categories. The paper also discusses achieving the theoretical upper bound, which involves optimization and algorithms, making it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on understanding the relationship between max-flow and min-cut in half-duplex broadcast networks with cycles could also place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SI) sub-category.
